.TH start-cli-package-backup-restore-mixed 1  "restore-mixed " 
.SH NAME
start\-cli\-package\-backup\-restore\-mixed \- Restore one selection of manual and automatic backup checkpoints
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBstart\-cli package backup restore\-mixed\fR [\fB\-\-manual\-ids\fR] [\fB\-\-checkpoint\fR] [\fB\-\-server\-id\fR] [\fB\-\-password\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fITARGET_ID\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Restore one selection of manual and automatic backup checkpoints
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-manual\-ids\fR \fI<MANUAL_IDS>\fR
Package identifiers
.TP
\fB\-\-checkpoint\fR \fI<PACKAGE_ID=SNAPSHOT_ID>\fR
Checkpoint as PACKAGE_ID=SNAPSHOT_ID; repeat for multiple services
.TP
\fB\-\-server\-id\fR \fI<SERVER_ID>\fR
Unique server identifier
.TP
\fB\-\-password\fR \fI<PASSWORD>\fR
Password for backup encryption
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fITARGET_ID\fR>
Backup target identifier
